Former Hong Kong Security Chief, John Lee, is tipped to be the special administrative region's next chief executive. In front of him is a city that has undergone drastic change and upheaval, from Western-backed anti-government riots to a global pandemic which has severely strained the socio-economic situation of the international financial hub. The question to the next chief executive is simple, but not easy. Voters ask: How can he turn Hong Kong's fortunes around? How can the city regain stability and prosperity?